============================================================

Self-review of the three changes:

**Implementation Completeness:** All three changes are real algorithm fixes — no mocks. Each directly addresses a root cause identified in the improvement plan.

**Code Quality:**
- Change 1 (suffix removal): The refactor from an implicit `return !survivingJoins.some(...)` to named `isPrefixOfJoin`/`isSuffixOfJoin` booleans is cleaner and more readable. Both conditions use the same pattern (check endpoints + continuation char guard).
- Change 2 (`normalize_separators`): Simple, single-purpose helper. Called correctly in both `extracted_norm` and `expected_parts` paths. The `+` split happens before normalization, so multi-title filenames are unaffected.
- Change 3 (hard disqualification): `-1.0` is well below any plausible embedding score, so `FRON WHEAT BUNS` can never win. The comment explains the intent.

**Integration:** All changes slot into existing code flow at the right places — no dead code, no bypassed logic.

**Codebase Consistency:** TypeScript side matches the existing style (arrow functions, early returns, lowercase comparisons). Python side follows the existing `normalize` helper pattern.

No concerns. The changes are correct, minimal, and well-integrated.
