{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VRY83LtZkBcb1n4HVUdVpj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 20 tests pass. Here's what was changed:\n\n**`lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`:**\n1. **Change 1 (lines ~394-420):** Extended the `survivingJoins` block to also remove suffix fragments. Previously it only removed prefix singles (e.g. `\"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\"`); now it also removes suffix singles that start with a continuation character (e.g. `\"& Coriander\"`), preventing them from triggering the \"shorter wins\" dedup rule against the complete join.\n\n2. **Change 3 (line ~307):** Changed the truncation penalty from soft `-0.15` to hard disqualification (`-1.0`). Truncated OCR artifacts like `FRON WHEAT BUNS` can never win over `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK` regardless of embedding score distributions.\n\n**`tools/title-loop/title-loop.py`:**\n3. **Change 2 (`titles_match`):** Added `normalize_separators()` that maps `:` → `/` before comparing. This accounts for the filesystem character substitution where `:` replaces `/` in filenames. The algorithm correctly outputs `/` from OCR; the evaluator now recognizes it as matching the `:` variant in the filename."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":386,"cache_read_input_tokens":36241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":386},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c824ccae-9243-4a33-a15e-6098977c30d8","uuid":"5447df75-512f-4dee-b089-7fb459e08f92"}
